-- Allstate Has Work to Do at Life Insurance Unit, CEO Wilson Says
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-12-04T13:54:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-04/allstate-has-work-to-do-at-life-insurance-unit-ceo-wilson-says.html
Allstate Corp. (ALL) , the largest publicly
traded seller of home and auto coverage in the U.S., will focus
on improving life insurance results to meet targets for return
on equity, Chief Executive Officer Thomas Wilson said.  “We have more work to do” at the life unit of the
Northbrook, Illinois-based insurer, Wilson said today at a
conference sponsored by Goldman Sachs Group Inc. in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  